sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I715010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: UV5 hybrid pLac promoter inserted in front of our promoter tester to test its promotion ability in vivo
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Michael Waters

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I715003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This promoter sequence is a derivative of part BBa_R0011 which is a -35 and -10 recognition site with two lac operator 1's inserted in the spacer region of the RNAP recognition region and before the -35 RANP recognition region. This part utilizes the UV5 double mutation at the -10 RNAP recognition site to recruit RNAP without the help of a CAP binding region.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The length of the fragment makes it cumbersome to gel purify
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Michael Waters

sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:title: UV5 -10 RNAP recognition region double mutation

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: KanR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: If there is a promoter and an RBS before this region, the cell will express Kanamycin resistance. As it has full biobricks, you can easily add KanR to an existing part without changing the plasmid vector,
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part is cloned in plasmid pSB1A2.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erin Zwack, Sabriya Rosemond

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Built by Josh as an intermediate in screening plasmid construction.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: jkm

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: tetA(C)f
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the coding region of the TetR gene. It requires a promoter and RBS for the cell to be able to express tetracyline resistance.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It was cloned into PsB1A2 plamsid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sabriya Rosemond, Erin Zwack
